cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories, as it deals with the problem of simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) in 3D space. Additionally, the paper introduces a differentiable computational graph approach to SLAM, which involves leveraging automatic differentiation capabilities, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories as well.
